article.headline: High Point 71, Coastal Carolina 63
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. (AP) -- Arizona Reid scored 20 points -- 14 in the first half -- to help High Point to a 71-63 Big South Conference win over Coastal Carolina on Saturday night. Eugene Harris had 11 and Landon Quick scored 10, while Cruz Daniels scored eight points, grabbed a career-high 12 rebounds and had three blocked shots for the Panthers (18-8, 8-2 Big South). Jerald Minnis had nine rebounds and seven points. Coastal (13-12, 6-5) was led by Joshua Mack with 16 points, including four 3-pointers. Jack Leasure scored 15 points and Moses Sonko scored 14 for the Chanticleers and Joseph Harris collected nine rebounds. High Point's win came before a sold-out crowd of 1,721 as the Panthers kept their second place in the conference and boosted their home record to 12-1 for the season.
